On duty at Willetn Point, N. Y., from July 23, 1875 to April 14, 1876;

At General Recruiting Station, New York City, N. Y. Harrisonburg,

Va., and accompanying Recruits to the Department of California, from

April 15 to May 21, 1876;

In the Department of Arizona, from June 1, 1876 to May 10, 1880, dur-

ing which period was at Fort Yuma, California, June 1 to August 5,

1876;

In the Department of the East, from September 1, 1880 to November

17, 1882, during which period was on duty at Creedmoor, Long Island,

with Rifle Team, September 1 to 18, 1880;

In the Department of the East, August 5, 1887 to October 31, 1891,

during which period was on duty at Mt. Vernon Barracks, Alabama,

August 5, 1887 to October 6, 1890;

In the Department of Dakota from November 7, 1891 to August 31, 1893;

during which time was on duty at Fort Snelling, Kinn., November 7,

1891 to August 21, 1892; at Headquarters Department of Dakota, St.

Paul, Minn., as Attending Surgeon and Examiner of Recruits, August 21,

1892 to August 31, 1893;

En route to and on duty at Tampa, Fla., and Havana, Cuba. On inves-

tigation as to use of electrozone and germicide in Havana and return-

ing March 7, 1900 to April 3, 1900;
